headline: Federal leverage over Fannie, Freddie could shape Trump’s housing push
summary: Investing.com -- U.S. President Donald Trump called for government-backed mortgage giants Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac to “get Big Homebuilders going” over which analysts are gauging how much influence Washington could actually wield over builders struggling with high costs and soft demand.The Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA) oversees Fannie and Freddie, which could become a key pressure point, according to Barclays analysts.
